Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), hypoglycemia, low HbA1c, and marked proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria. Urine is abnormal in appearance and color, with low specific gravity, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Findings suggest possible acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired glucose handling and possible dehydration or catabolic state. Clinical correlation and further nephrological and metabolic evaluation are recommended.
